Description:
    Installs Angarium: writes config/initializers/angarium.rb and copies its
    migrations into db/migrate (or db/NAME_migrate for a multi-database setup).
    Idempotent: migrations that already exist are skipped, so re-running is
    safe.

    Pass --database=NAME to run Angarium on its own database. This sets
    config.database in the initializer and installs migrations into
    db/NAME_migrate instead of db/migrate, so a later `angarium:upgrade` run
    (e.g. after a gem update) still targets the right place without repeating
    the flag.

    Re-running this generator with a different --database than last time
    changes config/initializers/angarium.rb's contents, so Thor will prompt
    to overwrite it. Pass --force to skip the prompt in scripts/CI.

Example:
    bin/rails generate angarium:install

    This creates:
        config/initializers/angarium.rb

    and copies Angarium's migrations into db/migrate:
        create_angarium_endpoints.rb
        create_angarium_events.rb
        create_angarium_deliveries.rb
        create_angarium_delivery_attempts.rb

    bin/rails generate angarium:install --database=angarium

    This sets config.database = :angarium in the initializer and copies the
    migrations into db/angarium_migrate instead.
